## 📌 Project Overview
The purpose of this project is to showcase a practical understanding of ticket prioritization, queue management, 
and service desk documentation hygiene. This repository serves as a hands-on demonstration of my ability to manage, 
triage, and resolve incoming technical support requests by leveraging the **ITIL Incident Management Lifecycle**, 
standard **ITIL Categories**, and the **ITIL Incident Priority Matrix**[cite: 1].

Utilizing a Service Desk Simulator as a controlled sandbox environment,
I map out the complete technical reasoning, user communication, and troubleshooting workflows used to process user incidents[cite: 1]. While the simulator provides a streamlined model of an enterprise network, the primary objective of this project is to highlight the core professional methodologies of **triaging, remediating, and thoroughly documenting** the entire lifecycle of an IT support ticket[cite: 1].

---

## ⚙️ Core Frameworks & Methodologies Applied
*   **ITIL v4 Framework:** Adherence to standard incident lifecycle stages: Logging, Categorization, Prioritization, Diagnosis, Escalation, Resolution, and Closure[cite: 1].
*   **Data-Driven Prioritization:** Evaluating incident urgency and business impact systematically using a standard Priority Matrix rather than subjective guessing[cite: 1].
*   **Incident Triage & Queue Management:** Managing concurrent tickets efficiently to meet organizational Service Level Agreements (SLAs).
*   **Documentation Hygiene:** Crafting clear, audit-ready internal work notes and professional, empathetic customer-facing resolution summaries[cite: 1].

---

## 📊 The Governing ITIL Priority Matrix
To ensure objective triage during queue operations, all simulated incidents are evaluated against this established business matrix:

| Impact \ Urgency | High (Critical Block) | Medium (Work Impaired) | Low (Workaround Exists) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **High (Enterprise / Site-Wide)** | **P1 - Critical** | **P2 - High** | **P3 - Medium** |
| **Medium (Department / Team)** | **P2 - High** | **P3 - Medium** | **P4 - Low** |
| **Low (Single End-User)** | **P3 - Medium** | **P4 - Low** | **P4 - Low** |

